sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT patient_id) 
FROM diagnoses 
WHERE diagnosis_name = 'Heart Disease';

SELECT DISTINCT mr.patient_id, mr.heart_disease
FROM medical_records mr
INNER JOIN treatment_plans tp ON mr.patient_id = tp.patient_id;

SELECT speciality, COUNT(*) AS number_of_doctors
FROM doctors
GROUP BY speciality;

external_knowledge:
Seasoned travelers through the journey of medication: refers to patients who have been on a medication treatment for more than 30 days;
Path they are following (medication and dosage): refers to the combination of the medication name and its prescribed dosage;
Length of their voyage so far: refers to the number of days since they started their current medication treatment.

- "sailors navigating under the stars" metaphorically refers to patients with first names and last names;
- "maps of their voyages" metaphorically refers to the diagnosis and treatment plans;
- "quality of their adherence to these maps" metaphorically refers to the compliance with the treatment plans.

- "numerous medical visits" refers to patients with more than 10 appointments;
- "flagged as needing ongoing monitoring" indicates that follow-ups are required ('Yes' in the database);
- "serious condition like heart disease" is a direct reference to the diagnosis name 'Heart Disease'.

sql:
SELECT p.first_name, p.last_name, m.medication_name
FROM patients p
JOIN medications m ON p.patient_id = m.patient_id;
